All Grassroots Alliance (AGA) gubernatorial candidate in Oyo State, Dr. David Oluwafemi Okunlola, has congratulated the governor-elect, Seyi Makinde. Makinde, who ran on the platform of Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) won the election by polling 515,621 votes, to defeat Adebayo Adelabu of the All Progressives Congress (APC), who scored 357,982 votes. In a statement yesterday Okunola said,  “On behalf of myself and my family, I congratulate the Governor Elect of Oyo State, Oluwaseyi Abiodun Makinde on your victory in the just concluded Governorship Election. “Your administration shall herald the much-anticipated development in Oyo State. The new dawn shall herald peace and progress for Oyo people and the nation at large.” To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .